Source: modbus-tk
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Antonio Parrella <zidagartsk@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7.0.50~), python (>= 2.6.6-3~), python-setuptools
Section: python
Standards-Version: 3.9.2
Homepage: http://code.google.com/p/modbus-tk/

Package: python-modbus-tk
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${python:Depends}, python-kinterbasdb
Provides: ${python:Provides}
Description: implementation of modbus protocol in python
 Modbus Test Kit provides implementation of slave and master
 for Modbus TCP and RTU.
 The main goal is to be used as testing tools.
 It can also be used to create any application which need to communicate
 over modbus.
 It is a full-stack implementation and is used on "real applications".
 .
 This package provide all necessary libraries.


Package: python-modbus-tk-doc
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Section: doc
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: modbus Test Kit documentation
 Modbus Test Kit provides implementation of slave and master
 for Modbus TCP and RTU.
 The main goal is to be used as testing tools.
 It can also be used to create any application which need to communicate
 over modbus.
 It is a full-stack implementation and is used on "real applications".
 .
 This package provide html documentation API and some examples.
